21/11/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The BiH Court has ordered a one-month detention for a Bosnian Serb charged with crimes against humanity, according to a court statement Monday (November 20th). Mladen Blagojevic, a former member of the Republika Srpska army's Laka Bratunac infantry brigade, is accused in connection with the 1995 Srebrenica massacre. He allegedly helped separate men from women and children, imprisoned men in Bratunac and Grabovci, and murdered at least five prisoners in Bratunac. (PBS BiH, NTV Hayat, Fena - 20/11/06)
